  "abstract": "Cultivated peanut, also known as groundnut (Arachis hypogaea L.), is grown on 25.5 million hectares between latitudes 40\" Nand 40° S with a total global production of 35 million Ions (MOO). Peanuts originated in South America; however, the vast majority of peanut is produced in Asia (66.8%: 23.4 Mt) /lndia Africa (24.6%: 8.6 MI). The remaining 8,6% (3 Mt) comes from North America, the Caribbean, Europe, and Oceania",
